President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. Rafael Borras was nominated for Under Secretary for Management at the Department of Homeland Security. James L. Hudson was nominated for Director of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development. Brenda Dann-Messier was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Vocational and Adult Education at the Department of Education. Dr. Kerri-Ann Jones was nominated for Assistant Secretary of State for Oceans and International Environmental and Scientific Affairs at the Department of State. Bryan H. Samuels was nominated for Commissioner of the Administration on Children, Youth and Families at the Health and Human Services. Christopher A. Hart was nominated for Member of the National Transportation Safety Board. President Obama expressed gratitude for their decision to serve the country and stated that their expertise and commitment make them valuable additions to the team as they work to confront challenges.